cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS

The paper discusses a model of meaning based on categorical methods, which is relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also presents techniques for building vector spaces, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves mathematical constructions and experimental evaluations, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively.
